title: Killer whales 'tear bits off boat' in 'scary' hour-long attack off Spanish coast
description: Orcas severely damaged a yacht off the coast of southern Spain - the latest in one of a number of killer whale attacks on vessels in the area.

title: Celine Dion 'heartbroken' as she cancels rest of world tour
description: Celine Dion has said "it breaks my heart" after cancelling the remaining concerts of her world tour because of a rare neurological illness.

title: 'Killer' bear spared death after being linked to two attacks on humans
description: A bear that was due to be killed after being blamed for the death of a runner has been granted a reprieve by an Italian court.

title: Two killed in 'Russian air strike' on Ukrainian health clinic and vets
description: At least two people have been killed after a Russian missile strike hit a health clinic and a veterinary building in eastern Ukraine, officials have said.

title: Passenger opens plane door mid-flight
description: A passenger opened a door on a South Korean plane shortly before it landed, officials have said.

title: Elon Musk's brain chip company says it has won approval for human testing
description: Elon Musk's brain chip firm Neuralink has said it has been given the go-ahead to start carrying out studies on humans.

title: Pink Floyd star Roger Waters condemned over 'Nazi costume' at Berlin concert
description: Police in Germany have launched an investigation into Pink Floyd co-founder Roger Waters after he fired an imitation machine gun while wearing a Nazi-inspired uniform at a concert in Berlin.

title: Boy, 11, 'shot in the chest' by police officer he had called for help
description: An 11-year-old boy who was shot by a police officer has returned home from hospital after almost a week of treatment.

title: Gabby Petito's family get copy of 'burn after reading' letter written by Brian Laundrie's mother
description: Brian Laundrie's mother offered him "a shovel and garbage bags" if he needed to dispose of a body, according to a "burn after reading" letter, court documents show.
